description:
went to ISA for our friends aniversary,   tried and shared a bunch of dishes with a bottle of wine, we/they really enjoyed themselves.  

started with the oysters, fish ceviche, both solid;  then had the asparagus soup,  tasty; 

for the mains we had Seared Foie Gras,small piece but excellent with the white peaches;  Seared Duck Breast, yep give me more huckleberry;    baked butterfish, delicious with the right hint of mushrooms; Grilled Flat Iron Steak,  good;  Seared Dayboat Scallops, ordered  after we were just about finished.  wow smelled amazing and cook to perfection;


dessert:  flowerless chocolate cake,  fluffy and not to sweet, great.

great ambiance, service good,  a bit pricey and certain plates were really small.  but overall a great place to go to.

check it out for that dining experience
